 "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def minOperations(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        n = len(nums)\n        operations = 0\n        \n        # Iterate through the array\n        for i in range(n - 2):\n            # If the current element is 0, we need to flip it and the next two elements\n            if nums[i] == 0:\n                # Perform the flip\n                nums[i] = 1\n                nums[i + 1] = 1 - nums[i + 1]\n                nums[i + 2] = 1 - nums[i + 2]\n                # Increment the operation count\n                operations += 1\n        \n        # Check if the last two elements are 1\n        if nums[-2] != 1 or nums[-1] != 1:\n            return -1\n        \n        return operations\n```\n\nThis solution iterates through the array and checks each element. If it encounters a `0`, it flips that element and the next two elements, counting the operation. After processing, it checks if the last two elements are `1`. If not, it returns `-1` indicating it's impossible to make all elements `1`. Otherwise, it returns the count of operations performed.", "estimated_date": 1718496000000}